# ZenRouter Query Parameters

## Base Setup

All routes extend `AppRoute` which mixes in `RouteQueryParameters`. Every route constructor must forward queries via `{super.queries}`.

```dart
class MyRoute extends AppRoute {
  MyRoute({required this.id, super.queries});
  final String id;
}
```

`parseRouteFromUri` must pass `uri.queryParameters` to every route constructor.

## Reading & Updating Queries

- Read: `query('key')` or `queries` getter
- Update: `updateQueries(coordinator, queries: {...queries, 'key': 'value'})` ‚Äî this updates `queryNotifier`, syncs the browser URL, and does NOT trigger a full navigation transition
- URL identity: `identifier` getter appends queries to `toUri()`, so the URL always reflects current query state

## Granular Rebuilds with selectorBuilder

Use `selectorBuilder` instead of `ValueListenableBuilder(valueListenable: queryNotifier)` to rebuild only when a derived value changes:

```dart
route.selectorBuilder<String?>(
  selector: (q) => q['filter'],
  builder: (context, filter) => Text('Filter: $filter'),
)
```

## One-Way Bloc Communication (Critical)

Data flow is strictly **route queries ‚Üí bloc**, never the reverse.

```
URL  ‚îÄ‚îÄparse‚îÄ‚îÄ>  queryNotifier  ‚îÄ‚îÄlistener‚îÄ‚îÄ>  bloc.onFiltersChanged()
                      ‚îÇ                              ‚îÇ
                 selectorBuilder              ListenableBuilder
                 (chips / tags)             (filtered data list)
```

### Pattern

```dart
// In StatefulWidget.initState ‚Äî attach ONE-WAY listener
route.queryNotifier.addListener(_syncToBloc);
_syncToBloc(); // initial sync

void _syncToBloc() => bloc.onFiltersChanged(route.queries);
```

### Rules
1. The bloc/controller NEVER calls `updateQueries` ‚Äî only UI event handlers do
2. `queryNotifier` is the single source of truth for filter state
3. Bloc reads filters from the listener callback, fetches data, and exposes results
4. If bloc wrote back to queries, it would create an infinite loop

## Sub-Route Filter Editing Pattern

When a sub-route (e.g. `/filter`) edits the parent's filters:

1. Push the filter route with current queries: `coordinator.push(FilterRoute(queries: queries))`
2. Filter route uses `updateQueries` on itself for live URL sync as user edits
3. On save, navigate back: `coordinator.navigate(ParentRoute(queries: route.queries))`
   - ZenRouter calls `onUpdate` on the existing parent, which copies `queryNotifier.value` from the new instance
4. On cancel, just `coordinator.tryPop()` ‚Äî parent keeps its original queries
